Package rpc.model.util

Class Summary
AttributeVariable A variable based on an attribute of a schema item.
Dependency A Dependency object holds information about a dependency in the model, including which unit supports the dependency and which Vertex objects the dependency connects.
Model Model object holds the set of known dependencies.
ModelSupport ModelSupport is a data structure that consists of all units, all possible dependencies in that space of units, information about potential causes, caches that store the standardization of units, and which units have been marked as dependent or independent.
ModelVisualizer This class translates the dependencies within a model into the dot visualization language.
StructureVariable A variable based on the structure of the schema.
Variable Abstract skeleton of a variable, which has a source item from the schema.
Vertex A vertex is an abstract representation of all versions of a particular variable (attribute or structure).
VertexPair A wrapper object that holds two underlying Vertex objects with a given order.
VertexTriple A wrapper object that holds three underlying Vertex objects with a given order.
